         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ Melbourne Bot Garden ¶ 5/1/71 ¶  ¶ The Capt. of the Ship "Geo. Thompson" has been so kind to promise to look after a small case full of plants, intended for you; ¶  or rather his wife is to exercis...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">71.01.05</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To [Joseph Hooker] </p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-81, f. 1.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Correspondent assumed to be J. Hooker as the letter is informing Kew that plants had been sent. There is no other similar letter addressed to another Kew officer. MS annotation <seg style="color: #000000; ">at head of letter: 'ansd thanked and list returned </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">
                        <hi rend="underline">19/4/71 J.S.</hi>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">' [John Smith (1821-88)].</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <seg style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>Melbourne Bot Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">5/1/71</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Capt. of the Ship "Geo. Thompson" has been so kind to promise to look after a small case full of plants, intended for you;<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">See M to J. Hooker, January 1871 (in this edition as 71-01-00).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> or rather his wife is to exercise the vigilance over them. Be so kind to send for the case, when the Ship arrives in London.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Your regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS <seg style="color: #000000; ">annotation beneath valediction: 'case received April 1871 only five plants alive J. Smith'.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
